What you’re describing is a horizontal scrollable toolbar—very common in modern apps 👍
You just need to wrap your buttons in a horizontal scroll container.

Below are the clean ways to do it depending on your stack 👇

⸻

✅ 1. Core Idea (Framework-agnostic)

You need:
	•	A container with horizontal overflow enabled
	•	A row layout
	•	Touch scrolling enabled (mobile)

⸻

💻 2. If you’re using HTML / CSS (Bolt, Web App, etc.)

✅ Basic Implementation

<div class="scroll-container">
  <button>Icon 1</button>
  <button>Icon 2</button>
  <button>Icon 3</button>
  <button>Icon 4</button>
  <button>Icon 5</button>
  <button>Icon 6</button>
</div>

.scroll-container {
  display: flex;
  overflow-x: auto;
  overflow-y: hidden;
  gap: 10px;
  padding: 10px;

  /* Smooth mobile scrolling */
  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;

  /* Optional: hide scrollbar */
  scrollbar-width: none;
}

.scroll-container::-webkit-scrollbar {
  display: none;
}


⸻

✅ Important Fixes (Common Problems)

If scrolling doesn’t work, check:

.scroll-container {
  white-space: nowrap;   /* ensures horizontal flow */
}

.scroll-container button {
  flex: 0 0 auto;        /* prevents shrinking */
}


⸻

⚡ 3. If you’re using React (Bolt / Next.js)

<div className="flex overflow-x-auto gap-3 p-2">
  {icons.map((icon, i) => (
    <button key={i} className="flex-shrink-0">
      {icon}
    </button>
  ))}
</div>

Tailwind version (best for Bolt)

<div className="flex overflow-x-auto whitespace-nowrap gap-3 px-2 py-2 scrollbar-hide">


⸻

📱 4. Make It Feel Native (Very Important)

Add this for smooth finger scrolling:

.scroll-container {
  scroll-behavior: smooth;
  touch-action: pan-x;
}


⸻

✨ 5. Optional Enhancements (Highly Recommended)

🔹 Snap scrolling (feels premium)

.scroll-container {
  scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
}

.scroll-container button {
  scroll-snap-align: start;
}


⸻

🔹 Add fade edges (pro UI look)

Gives a hint that content is scrollable.

.scroll-container {
  mask-image: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, black 20%, black 80%, transparent);
}


⸻

🔹 Add arrows (desktop usability)

<button onclick="scrollLeft()">←</button>
<button onclick="scrollRight()">→</button>


⸻

🧠 UX Tip (Important for your app)

Since you’re building a lesson / AI app UI, consider:
	•	Group icons (don’t overload one row)
	•	Add labels under icons
	•	Use “active state” highlighting
	•	Add auto-scroll to selected item

⸻

🚀 Best Practice for Your App (Recommended Setup)

Use:
	•	flex
	•	overflow-x-auto
	•	flex-shrink-0
	•	hidden scrollbar
	•	snap scrolling

This gives a Netflix-style horizontal menu 👍

⸻

🔥 If you want next step

I can:
	•	Build a full Bolt UI component (copy-paste ready)
	•	Add gesture inertia + snapping + active state
	•	Or design your entire toolbar system (like YouTube/Netflix)

Just tell me 👍

